<b>There is a select drop down on a webpage for which you donâ€™t know the tag at all how will you find it?</b>

1. Use a broad XPath and then verify the element type:
List<WebElement> elements = driver.findElements(By.xpath("//*"));
for (WebElement el : elements) {
    if (el.getTagName().equalsIgnoreCase("select") || 
        el.getAttribute("role").equalsIgnoreCase("dropdown")) {
        System.out.println("Dropdown found: " + el);
    }
}
2. Use relative locators:
WebElement label = driver.findElement(By.xpath("//label[text()='Country']"));
// Find element below the label (could be <select>, <div>, etc.)
WebElement dropdown = driver.findElement(with(By.tagName("*")).below(label));
// Now interact
dropdown.click();  // For custom dropdowns

<b>You have three tables employee(empid,empname,address,exp)
<b>salary(empid,salary,deptid) department(deptid,deptname). Find the 3rd highest salary

SELECT e.empid,
       e.empname,
       s.salary,
       d.deptname
FROM (
    SELECT empid,
           salary,
           deptid,
           DENSE_RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY deptid ORDER BY salary DESC) AS sal_rank
    FROM salary
) s
JOIN employee e ON e.empid = s.empid
JOIN department d ON d.deptid = s.deptid
WHERE s.sal_rank = 3;

 
